Beached v.

Having been, or currently being on a beach and unable to retreat back into the water.

An example of this would be a beached whale. Beached whales swim into water that is too shallow and become stuck on the beach. They are unable to move under their own power.

However,beached can also refer to a myriad of animals such as dolphins, sharks, sea lions, seals as well as man-made devises such as a kayak, canoe, ship, scooner, submarine, boat or tanker.